  <bioghist id="c7c0c39cc2911243ef50701f736d9159">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Esther Roditti Schachter (1933-2017) was a lawyer who worked for several years as a Program Officer in the Ford Foundation's Division of National Affairs, Government and Law Program. After leaving the Ford Foundation, Roditti entered the computer law field. She founded the Computer Law and Tax Report newsletter and established a private practice.</p><p>Roditti also had an interest in environmental law. Her work "Enforcing Air Pollution Controls: Case Study of New York City" was published in 1974. Prior to joining the Ford Foundation, she had positions at The New School for Social Research and Columbia University. She earned her B.A. from the University of California, Los Angeles and earned her law degree from Harvard Law School.</p>  </bioghist>
